{"questionId":"21466","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>A tank of water initially contains <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>400</mn></math> litres. Water is leaking from the tank such that after&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>10</mn></math> minutes there are <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>324</mn></math> litres remaining in the tank.</p>\n<p>The volume of water, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>V</mi></math> litres, remaining in the tank after <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>t</mi></math> minutes, can be modelled by the&nbsp;differential equation</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mo>d</mo><mi>V</mi></mrow><mrow><mo>d</mo><mi>t</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mi>k</mi><msqrt><mi>V</mi></msqrt></math>, where&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>k</mi></math>&nbsp;is a constant.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Find the time taken for the tank to empty.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>0</mn><mo>=</mo><msup><mfenced><mrow><mn>20</mn><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mi>t</mi><mn>5</mn></mfrac></mrow></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>⇒</mo><mi>t</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>100</mn></math>&nbsp;minutes&nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;(M1)A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><em><strong><br>[2 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"21466","referenceCode":"21M.1.AHL.TZ1.12b","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"Find the time taken for the tank to empty.","paper":"1","level":"HL","questionNumber":"b","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 5—Calculus","Topic 5—Calculus","AHL 5.14—Setting up a DE, solve by separating variables"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}